<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="841" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0093/12–848: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-08">December 8, 1948</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                December 8—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2450. Marine plane with last group Nanking dependents departed today at
                            0730.</p>
                        <p>Sent Manila 54, repeated Department 2450.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>